result.execSummary:
The defendant Jason S Kieleszewski was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Attempt Theft-False Representation <=$2500, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(d).
  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Jason S. Kieleszewski in court with attorney Anne Renc. Cass W Cousins appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
2:03 p.m.  Court calls the case. 

State files amended information. 
Plea questionnaire/Agreement filed.
Prosecutor states plea agreement.
Attorney for Defendant concurs with agreement stated.

Defendant enters a plea of:  Counts 1 & 2 of the Amended Information - NO CONTEST

Court questions Defendant regarding plea.
Court informs Defendant of Constitutional Rights. Court advises Defendant of Elements State must prove for the Charge.
Court questions Attorney for Defendant.
Court finds Defendant's Plea is freely, voluntarily and intelligently made.
Attorneys stipulate that there is factual basis for the charge(s).

BY THE COURT:
Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charge(s).
Court finds the defendant guilty Counts 1 & 2.  Clerk directed to enter Judgment of Conviction this date.

Atty Cousins makes sentencing arguments to the Court. 
Atty Renc makes sentencing arguments to the Court. 

BY THE COURT:
On each count, concurrent with each other: 
60 days jail STAYED
Huber for work, counseling and any other reason the sheriff will allow. 
Allowed to serve 1/2 of the sentence on electronic monitor if he qualifies. 
Placed on probation for 12 months, concurrent to any other probation he is serving. 
Pay fine of $200 plus costs on Count 1 including the DNA surcharge. 
Provide DNA sample. 
Count 2 - Costs including the DNA Surcharge. 
Participate in any other assessments deemed appropriate by the agent.
